<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7269&amp;p=71474#p71474"><![CDATA[
C, C++, Java, PHP, and numerous other C-family languages make a distinction between bitwise AND (&amp;) and logical AND (&amp;&amp;). Bitwise AND is the operation performed here. Logical AND is "1 if both values are nonzero; otherwise 0". I just rewrote much of that section to get more of the discussion out of the bit chart.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Dec 15, 2010 8:31 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
